tweet_raw: This clip is actually quite illustrative of how insanely incestuous French elites have become.Its a bit hard to follow so bear with me. So theres a new scandal in France because the new minister of education Amélie Oudéa-Castera put her kids in a very elitist private school which she justified it with a comment that was very disparaging of the public education system (despite her now being in charge of managing the public education system). She said she did so because her kids used to be in a public school but the teachers were often calling sick and the missing hours were never being covered. Which has been demonstrated as a lie but thats besides the point...The interesting fact is that in this clip the journalist interrogating her guests on this subject - Apolline de Malherbe - is the cousin of Frances new prime minister Gabriel Attal who nominated the minister at her post. Thats incestuousness level 1.The guest shes interrogating about this Nicolas Poincaré is another famous French journalist whos interrogated because he had his kids in the same school as the minister. Incestuousness level 2. Nicolas Poincaré is by the way a living representation of Frances reproduction of elites because he is the great-grandson of mathematician Henri Poincaré and grandnephew of the French President Raymond Poincaré.The minister herself - Amélie Oudéa-Castera - comes from the same small French elite caste because her father was the CEO of Publicis - one of Frances largest companies - and her mother the companys HR director. She also happens to be the niece of Alain Duhamel and of Nathalie Saint-Cricq two of Frances most famous journalists. And shes married with Frédéric Oudéa formerly CEO of Société générale bank and now CEO of Sanofi. Incestuousness level 3.And Gabriel Attal the 34-year old Prime Minister who nominated her - who as a reminder is the cousin of the journalist here 👇- himself comes from the same small elite caste: his father comes from the family of the owners of Galeries Lafayette and was a journalist from Le Monde as well as a movie producer. Attal went to the very elitist École Alsacienne school in central Paris where many kids from this small elite cast study.And cherry on the cake besides nominating Oudéa-Castera as minister of education Attal also just nominated his ex-husband Stéphane Séjourné as minister of foreign affairs!Just an illustration of how Frances politico-mediatic-business class is increasingly a small incestuous group of people all connected with each others throughout generations... Which is obviously insanely unhealthy as a society. Were progressively going back to the aristocratic time of the king and his court...

Less than a week after the United States Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) approved 11 spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds (ETFs) and trading kicked off on respective stock exchanges the sell-the-news narrative is already visible. tweet_raw: WTF Are Bitcoin Runes? ®️🪄🪙Heres a detailed explanation.Casey Rodarmor the provocative mastermind behind Bitcoin Ordinals re-emerges after a period of low public engagement since March unveiling a new concept named Runes. With the phenomenal success of Ordinals—boasting 34M inscriptions 605k holders (GeniiData) and $550M in trading volume (CryptoSlam) the introduction of Runes has shaken up the crypto space once again.Core Concept of Runes:Runes is an innovative fungible token protocol on Bitcoin functioning as an alternative to BRC-20s and several other protocols. Its a solution that uses more of Bitcoins native functionality is far more efficient scalable and secure. It also has a greater compatibility with other Bitcoin-based protocols like Lightning and DLCs unlocking new capabilities.New Paradigm for Recording Data:The protocol diverges from all existing fungible token standards by operating on-chain and being UTXO-based avoiding the development challenges with off-chain and address-based approaches when working with Bitcoin. Runes embed the record of balances directly in the UTXOs rather than linking to wallet addresses making computation an order of magnitude simpler. The use of OP_RETURN in Runes protocol as opposed to the Witness in Ordinals eliminates certain complications and ensures the autonomy of Runes from Ordinals while this independence means starting a base of nodes is more challenging it also means Runes might be able to combine with Ordinals for innovative functionality.Practical Example:The real-world application of Runes is intuitive. For instance a UTXO with any number of satoshis can contain any number of Runes. If a user wishes to send 100k Runes to two friends you can do it in one transaction splitting the UTXO into three each containing the assigned Runes with these details managed via OP_RETURN in the Bitcoin transaction.Faster & More Secure Metaprotocol Development:The biggest implication of Runes is that it will be easier for developers to build DeFi and other smart contract-like use cases on top of compared to existing protocols. These metaprotocols will benefit from simpler architecture of Runes with an order of magnitude faster data indexing (seconds vs days) thanks to its UTXO-based approach leveraging Bitcoins existing data architecture. These protocols will be more secure as well due to using more of Bitcoins native features and less of a reliance on indexers.Narrative Violation:Runes encounters potential standardness rules violations due to its use of OP_RETURNs larger than 80 bytes. However as Casey indicates this doesn’t impact block validity and miners will likely accept such transactions if they are lucrative. Casey’s Runes breaks predefined notions of building on Bitcoin making Runes a potential game-changer.Benefits & Compatibility:Casey envisions Runes contributing fees to strengthen Bitcoin and attracting more users and developers from different blockchains. Runes have a minimal on-chain footprint and promote responsible UTXO management making them good for Bitcoin. The compatibility with both Lightning and DLCs grants Runes a competitive edge possibly introducing new dimensions for developers.Community Response & Development Speed:The announcement of Runes sent ripples through the Ordinals community the concept labeled as “a terrible idea” by Casey himself garnered overwhelming response and enthusiasm. From the announcement of his half-baked blog post to the issuance of the first Rune token $RUNE the development unfolded in less than seven hours—a remarkable feat for blockchain developments.

tweet_text: cryptos and their mechanisms decoding the protocols   proof of work pow  1bitcoin btc the pioneer and flagship cryptocurrency bitcoin relies on pow to secure its network and validate transactions  2dogecoin doge originally based on litecoins technology doge also uses pow for transaction validation  3ethereum classic etc etc a fork of ethereum employs pow as its consensus mechanism to secure the blockchain  4litecoin ltc created as the silver to bitcoins gold litecoin utilizes pow for its transaction validation  5monero xmr xmr prioritizes privacy and anonymity using pow allowing for confidential transactions  proof of stake pos  1ethereum eth ethereum is transitioning to pos with ethereum 20 enhancing scalability and sustainability  2cardano ada ada employs pos emphasizing energy efficiency and decentralization in its consensus mechanism  3solana sol solana stands out for its high throughput and low transaction costs driven by a pos mechanism  4binance coin bnb bnb native to the binance smart chain utilizes pos for faster transaction confirmation  5polygon matic initially on ethereum matic has its own pos network aiming for scalability and reduced environmental impact  understanding these mechanisms is pivotal for evaluating a cryptocurrencys security scalability and environmental impact  cryptocurrencymechanisms proofofwork proofofstake cryptoinnovation
tweet_raw: Cryptos and Their Mechanisms: Decoding the Protocols! 🧩🔍Proof of Work (PoW):1.Bitcoin (BTC):•The pioneer and flagship cryptocurrency Bitcoin relies on PoW to secure its network and validate transactions.2.Dogecoin (DOGE):•Originally based on Litecoin’s technology DOGE also uses PoW for transaction validation.3.Ethereum Classic (ETC):•ETC a fork of Ethereum employs PoW as its consensus mechanism to secure the blockchain.4.Litecoin (LTC):•Created as the “silver to Bitcoin’s gold” Litecoin utilizes PoW for its transaction validation.5.Monero (XMR):•XMR prioritizes privacy and anonymity using PoW allowing for confidential transactions.Proof of Stake (PoS):1.Ethereum (ETH):•Ethereum is transitioning to PoS with Ethereum 2.0 enhancing scalability and sustainability.2.Cardano (ADA):•ADA employs PoS emphasizing energy efficiency and decentralization in its consensus mechanism.3.Solana (SOL):•Solana stands out for its high throughput and low transaction costs driven by a PoS mechanism.4.Binance Coin (BNB):•BNB native to the Binance Smart Chain utilizes PoS for faster transaction confirmation.5.Polygon (MATIC):•Initially on Ethereum MATIC has its own PoS network aiming for scalability and reduced environmental impact.Understanding these mechanisms is pivotal for evaluating a cryptocurrency’s security scalability and environmental impact. 🌐🛠️ #CryptocurrencyMechanisms #ProofOfWork #ProofOfStake #CryptoInnovation 🚀💡

tweet_text: polkadots industry breakthrough moment    is polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma     security ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation  polkadot has the 2 highest nakamoto coefficient behind bitcoin its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network   scalability the ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost  asynchronous backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks in terms of execution time while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds this reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously 100k1m tps   decentralization distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control  nominated proof of stake decentralized governance  the development of polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of dot token holders a council and a technical committee to make changes to the network the idea is to combine dot token holders and the council to administer network upgrade decisions dot securedbypolkadot
tweet_raw: Polkadots industry breakthrough moment 🚀🚀 Is Polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma?  ⭕️- Security: Ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation.*Polkadot has the #2 highest Nakamoto Coefficient behind Bitcoin. Its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network.- Scalability: The ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost.*Asynchronous Backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks (in terms of execution time) while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds. This reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously! 100k-1M TPS- Decentralization: Distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control.*Nominated Proof of Stake*Decentralized Governance*The development of Polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of DOT token holders a Council and a Technical Committee. To make changes to the network the idea is to combine DOT token holders and the Council to administer network upgrade decisions.#DOT #SecuredbyPolkadot

tweet_text: polkadots industry breakthrough moment    is polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma     security ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation  polkadot has the 2 highest nakamoto coefficient behind bitcoin its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network   scalability the ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost  asynchronous backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks in terms of execution time while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds this reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously 100k1m tps   decentralization distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control  nominated proof of stake decentralized governance  the development of polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of dot token holders a council and a technical committee to make changes to the network the idea is to combine dot token holders and the council to administer network upgrade decisions dot securedbypolkadot
tweet_raw: Polkadots industry breakthrough moment 🚀🚀 Is Polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma?  ⭕️- Security: Ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation.*Polkadot has the #2 highest Nakamoto Coefficient behind Bitcoin. Its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network.- Scalability: The ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost.*Asynchronous Backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks (in terms of execution time) while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds. This reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously! 100k-1M TPS- Decentralization: Distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control.*Nominated Proof of Stake*Decentralized Governance*The development of Polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of DOT token holders a Council and a Technical Committee. To make changes to the network the idea is to combine DOT token holders and the Council to administer network upgrade decisions.#DOT #SecuredbyPolkadot

tweet_text: polkadots industry breakthrough moment    is polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma     security ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation  polkadot has the 2 highest nakamoto coefficient behind bitcoin its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network   scalability the ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost  asynchronous backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks in terms of execution time while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds this reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously 100k1m tps   decentralization distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control  nominated proof of stake decentralized governance  the development of polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of dot token holders a council and a technical committee to make changes to the network the idea is to combine dot token holders and the council to administer network upgrade decisions dot securedbypolkadot
tweet_raw: Polkadots industry breakthrough moment 🚀🚀 Is Polkadot solving the blockchain trilemma?  ⭕️- Security: Ensuring that the network is resistant to attacks and data manipulation.*Polkadot has the #2 highest Nakamoto Coefficient behind Bitcoin. Its determined simply by counting the number of entities required to compromise a subsystem of a network.- Scalability: The ability to process a high volume of transactions efficiently and at low cost.*Asynchronous Backing enables parachains to have bigger blocks (in terms of execution time) while at the same time also shortening block times from twelve to six seconds. This reduces latency and multiplies possible throughput simultaneously! 100k-1M TPS- Decentralization: Distributing control across a wide network of participants to avoid central points of failure or control.*Nominated Proof of Stake*Decentralized Governance*The development of Polkadot is also decentralized governed by a distributed community of DOT token holders a Council and a Technical Committee. To make changes to the network the idea is to combine DOT token holders and the Council to administer network upgrade decisions.#DOT #SecuredbyPolkadot

tweet_raw: 🏆Welcome back to the NoBS Crypto TournamentToday weve got $AZERO vs $XLMCast your votes in the comments & well see which is the stronger community in the next 24 hoursNow lets get to a reminder of what IOTA & Quant aim to do!$AZERO is a Layer 1 blockchain network that uses the benefits of both a blockchain & a DAG.  There are a couple fundamental points that set Aleph Zero apart from its competition of other Layer 1 networks.  First is their networks consensus of AlephBFT this novel consensus mechanism is based off Proof of Stake but also leverages randomness in selecting validators.  Additionally their Liminal killer application truly makes Aleph Zeros network one of a kind.  As Liminal is like a pre-built Layer 2 within the Aleph Zero ecosystem that sits overtop of the network.  The goal of Liminal is to serve as a privacy and interoperability solution.  As Liminal is able to enable cross chain transfers of assets in addition to enabling private state smart contract data to stay contained on Aleph Zero Their unique approach is created by the team at Cardinal Cryptography which focuses on scientific & mathematical research in the DLT space.  The team is made up of the $AZERO core team & they even had a core role in creating $CSPR Highway consensus!  Over the past year weve seen continued development towards the Aleph Zero ecosystem.  From applications such as DRKVRS oracle integration & even Deutsche Telekom recently joining the ecosystem as a validator!$EWT is also a Layer 1 though their focus is specifically on the energy sector.Their goal is to create an immutable network in which energy assets are able to register with digital identities on-chain and tokenizing that energy data for real world use cases.The clean energy data is in the form of renewable energy certificates (RECs).As Energy Web is initially created by multiple energy industry leaders around the world theyve managed to connect and collaborate with the ones building standards around RECs.Their network consensus is quite unique as its closer to $HBAR council than any traditional validator ecosystem.This is because Energy Web has a dedicated group of validators for the network in fact their validator ecosystem is permissioned.This means that even if someone random wanted to validate for the $EWT ecosystem theyd need permission and be verified to be let in.The reason for this being that large energy players will want only the best responsible for the validation of data on the global energy grid.Over the past year Energy Web has progressed quite significantly with their SAFc solution alongside Shell.As weve seen JetBlue Emirates Airlines & Google all adopting the solution for cleaner aviation travel.Much like Aleph Zero Energy Webs ecosystem has also gained support and approval for Deutsche Telekom in the past year.Most notably their digital identity solution alongside energy transmission leader Elia Group had just recently been taken in and used as a framework by the Open Wallet Foundation!WHO WILL WIN?!Enterprise Privacy (AZERO) vs P2P Remittance (XLM)Dont forget to let me know below & stay tuned to see who makes it to the next round🔥

tweet_raw: Last week I was having breakfast at Chik-fil-A and as I was sitting in my truck eating I noticed a homeless guy sitting on the curb behind the building with his dog.He was holding a sign asking for money or food donations to help feed him and his dog (did not look like a druggy or alchy just an older man down on his luck). I observed him the entire time I ate my breakfast he mostly just sat there scratching his mutt and holding the sign while people drove past ignoring them. When I finished my breakfast I decided to make another run through the drive-through and ordered a large chicken biscuit combo. As I was leaving I pulled up along side him and handed him the bag of breakfast and a small bag of dog food I had in my truck for when I bring my dog to work.The bag of Chick-fil-A put a huge smile on his face but when I handed him the bag of dog food the guy literally lost it and started bawling right there on the side of my truck. After regaining his composure he exclaimed that it had been so long since somebody had treated him like a human being. I asked him if he would be willing to work hard for a decent day’s pay and he immediately straightened up and exclaimed that he could be the hardest worker I had ever seen. I gave him my business card and a fiver and told him to meet me at that spot the next morning and I would put him to work.The next day I stopped in and sure enough he was waiting there for me I took him and his dog to the jobsite. He wasn’t kidding about being a hard worker; this guy carried wood around and fetched tools out of my truck for me all day without complaining once. His dog just shadowed him the entire time.During the day I learned about how he had lost his wife in a car accident had his home that he had lived in for 35 years repossessed by the bank had no children or family was staying at a KOA campground and had a bunch of his life possessions stolen had been spit on by strangers while begging for money and had all but given up on the human race as a whole.At the end of the day I took him to my bank and withdrew his day’s pay which amounted to $80. The look on his face was well worth it. My random act of kindness seemed to put a spark back in his eye and I continued to pick him up the rest of the week in the same spot and paying him at the end of each day.Yesterday when I dropped him off he asked me to take him to a different spot near the KOA. He explained with the money I paid him he was going to be able to afford camping provisions for the next couple of months and told me how much it meant to him and his dog to not have to sleep outside on the cold ground.When I left him last night he looked like a different person then the man I saw hanging his head in shame behind Chik-fil-A. He promised me he would be there for me next week if I needed him and although my job-site is going to be on the other side of town next week I have already decided to continue going out of my way to pick him up and put him to work.Credit goes to the respective owner.

tweet_raw: Last week I was having breakfast at Chik-fil-A and as I was sitting in my truck eating I noticed a homeless guy sitting on the curb behind the building with his dog.He was holding a sign asking for money or food donations to help feed him and his dog (did not look like a druggy or alchy just an older man down on his luck). I observed him the entire time I ate my breakfast he mostly just sat there scratching his mutt and holding the sign while people drove past ignoring them. When I finished my breakfast I decided to make another run through the drive-through and ordered a large chicken biscuit combo. As I was leaving I pulled up along side him and handed him the bag of breakfast and a small bag of dog food I had in my truck for when I bring my dog to work.The bag of Chick-fil-A put a huge smile on his face but when I handed him the bag of dog food the guy literally lost it and started bawling right there on the side of my truck. After regaining his composure he exclaimed that it had been so long since somebody had treated him like a human being. I asked him if he would be willing to work hard for a decent day’s pay and he immediately straightened up and exclaimed that he could be the hardest worker I had ever seen. I gave him my business card and a fiver and told him to meet me at that spot the next morning and I would put him to work.The next day I stopped in and sure enough he was waiting there for me I took him and his dog to the jobsite. He wasn’t kidding about being a hard worker; this guy carried wood around and fetched tools out of my truck for me all day without complaining once. His dog just shadowed him the entire time.During the day I learned about how he had lost his wife in a car accident had his home that he had lived in for 35 years repossessed by the bank had no children or family was staying at a KOA campground and had a bunch of his life possessions stolen had been spit on by strangers while begging for money and had all but given up on the human race as a whole.At the end of the day I took him to my bank and withdrew his day’s pay which amounted to $80. The look on his face was well worth it. My random act of kindness seemed to put a spark back in his eye and I continued to pick him up the rest of the week in the same spot and paying him at the end of each day.Yesterday when I dropped him off he asked me to take him to a different spot near the KOA. He explained with the money I paid him he was going to be able to afford camping provisions for the next couple of months and told me how much it meant to him and his dog to not have to sleep outside on the cold ground.When I left him last night he looked like a different person then the man I saw hanging his head in shame behind Chik-fil-A. He promised me he would be there for me next week if I needed him and although my job-site is going to be on the other side of town next week I have already decided to continue going out of my way to pick him up and put him to work.Credit goes to the respective owner.

tweet_raw: Our two-way liquidity portalWhat is it? Its the first of its kind and only under our hybrid model.First whats the hybrid model?Its combining both NFTs and tokens into one what we call NFTxTOKEN.Our NFTs are inscribed onto the blockchain and they each hold 800000 tokens each. Think of the NFTs as bricks of gold you take them into the bank and swap them for cash in your wallet (our tokens).You can always take the cash to the bank and get your brick of gold back.Its exactly how our hybrid model operates.1 $bozo NFT = 800000 $bozo tokens and 800000 tokens = 1 $bozo NFTBoth are traded separately on their secondary markets and this is where the cross market arbitrage liquidity injection comes from. Arbitrage opportunities arise to keep 800000 $bozo tokens the same as 1 NFT.The two-way liquidity portals is the word we use for another portal of liquidity to enter our ecosystem. One through the NFT secondary markets like magic eden or tensor trade and the other through traditional token trading markets like raydium.This is revolutionary and has never been done before and opens up a whole new world of liquidity and game theory. As liquidity grows through market efficiencies youll be able to exit large positions very easily without slippage typically seen on token trading.
